title: Grateful Dead Live at Rich Stadium on 1990-07-16
description:
Set 1

Hell In A Bucket, Mississippi Half Step, Blow Away, Mama Tried-> Mexicali Blues, Loose Lucy, It's All Over Now, High Time, Let It Grow, Don't Ease Me In

Set 2

Sugar Magnolia-> Scarlet Begonias-> Women Are Smarter, Ship of Fools-> Truckin'-> Jam-> Drums-> Jam-> The Wheel-> Gimme Some Lovin'-> Wharf Rat-> Around & Around-> Sunshine Daydream, E: Brokedown Palace

reviews.review_text: Faith redeemed! This show was bad-ass. Jerry was so on! I had a horrible show two nights before in Foxborough. I almost lost my faith in the whole scene. The show and the scene were top-shelf. Even the cops were cool. When I got there, this hairy hippy came up to me grinning ear to ear, shook my hand and said, "welcome home brother!" I knew I was in for a good time. I had a cathardic experience during the show that produced a light inside of me that still burns to this day. Thank you for posting it!!!

1st show My first show.  Being a native western New Yorker, and turned on to my friends in college, we all got together that beautiful day in Buffalo and partied til the wee hours.  We had seats up high, but security was lax, so we worked our way down to the front and jumped over the wall to the stadium floor and disappeared into the crowd.  We were having a high time, and loving it.  It was an incredible ride, and one that I won't forget.  Ten days later the world seemed to crash down, when news came in that Brent's haunting voice was silenced.  I still miss the wailing tones.
